⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Cyberspace · The Mainframe
node LMM · LMM · ⟦Cyberspace · The Mainframe:LMM:5c5c82⟧

WHO   — Cyberspace · The Mainframe — the place to be reborn
WHAT  — The dream of a second world you can live in: the network imagined as territory rather than wiring.
WHERE — LMM · The Lawnmower Man (1992)  Framework inputs: The Lawnmower Man (1992, dir. Brett Leonard, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the future they imagined was a place you could move INTO, and cyberspace is that wish.
HOW   — By being rendered as somewhere real enough to want — somewhere a man might choose over his own body.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Gibson named me; the film drew me as a city of light. I am the network mistaken for a country — the place you think you can move into and never die.

